post_text:
Good afternoon Fairbanks Families,

Our 2020-2021 School Planning Work Groups have been diving into our process for opening school in August. Based on our family survey, 7% of our respondents indicated they would not return to a traditional school setting without a vaccine for COVID-19. We are looking at potential remote learning options to support these families.

If you are interested in a full-time remote option in Fairbanks for the 2020-2021 school year, please indicate your student(s) name and grade on the survey below. This data will help our district continue to plan for the upcoming school year and if we will be able to provide this option for families.

Only families interested in a remote learning option for the 2020-2021 school year should complete this survey.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdxbjMF_kjdaJygFUvTktBcZ6XNlwmE4vdw5VRoCAr_3ZLepA/viewform

If you have specific questions, please email Adham Schirg at adhamschirg@fairbankspnathers.org. Thank you for your continued help and feedback through this process!!

For Fairbanks,

Adham

Good afternoon! This is David Baits, Superintendent of Fairbanks Local Schools calling about a make-up day. Friday, February 1st was our 6th missed day of school this year. The district will follow the make-up schedule at the bottom of the Board approved 2018-19 calendar. Thus, Friday, February 15, 2019, is now a regular day of classes for all students in grades K-12. There will be no pre-school classes on this day.

School buses will run their regularly scheduled routes.

Thanks and have a great day!
